The '''Crystal chest''' can be found in the house directly south of the [[Witch's House (location)|Witch's House]] in [[Taverley]]. The chest is locked and can only be opened using a [[crystal key]], which is made by combining a [[loop half of key]] and a [[tooth half of key]]. Attempting to open the chest without the crystal key yields the message: ''This chest is securely locked shut.'' Opening the crystal chest grants an [[uncut dragonstone]] and a variety of other rewards.

Opening the crystal chest is a task for the medium [[Falador Diary]].

==Reward possibilities==
{{DropLogProject|kills=22483|type=openings}}

''The expected value of the crystal chest is {{Coins|
{{GEP|Uncut dragonstone}} +
34/128 * ({{GEP|Spinach roll}} + 2000) +
12/128 * ({{GEP|Air rune|50}} + {{GEP|Water rune|50}} + {{GEP|Earth rune|50}} + {{GEP|Fire rune|50}} + {{GEP|Body rune|50}} + {{GEP|Mind rune|50}} + {{GEP|Cosmic rune|10}} + {{GEP|Chaos rune|10}} + {{GEP|Nature rune|10}} + {{GEP|Law rune|10}} + {{GEP|Death rune|10}}) +
12/128 * ({{GEP|Ruby|2}} + {{GEP|Diamond|2}}) +
12/128 * {{GEP|Runite bar|3}} +
10/128 * {{GEP|Iron ore|150}} +
10/128 * {{GEP|Coal|100}} +
8/128 * ({{GEP|Raw swordfish|5}} + 1000) +
5/128 * ({{GEP|Tooth half of key}} + 750) +
5/128 * ({{GEP|Loop half of key}} + 750) +
2/128 * {{GEP|Adamant sq shield}} +
1/128 * (({{GEP|Rune platelegs}} + {{GEP|Rune plateskirt}})/2)}}. The cost of a crystal key currently is {{Coins|{{GEP|Crystal key}}}}, while the loop and tooth halves together will cost {{Coins|{{GEP|Tooth half of key}} + {{GEP|Loop half of key}}}}.''

